{
  "video_id": "IFjD3NMv6Kw",
  "title": "7 principles for building better cities | Peter Calthorpe",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12494.0,
      "end_time": 14476.0,
      "text": "So, let me add to the complexity"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14500.0,
      "end_time": 17660.0,
      "text": "of the situation we find ourselves in."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17900.0,
      "end_time": 21416.0,
      "text": "At the same time that we&#39;re solving for climate change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21440.0,
      "end_time": 25243.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to be building cities for three billion people."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26397.0,
      "end_time": 29500.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a doubling of the urban environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29727.0,
      "end_time": 31400.0,
      "text": "If we don&#39;t get that right,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31424.0,
      "end_time": 35955.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m not sure all the climate solutions in the world will save mankind,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 36627.0,
      "end_time": 40402.0,
      "text": "because so much depends on how we shape our cities:"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 40426.0,
      "end_time": 42656.0,
      "text": "not just environmental impacts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42680.0,
      "end_time": 44316.0,
      "text": "but our social well-being,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44340.0,
      "end_time": 46622.0,
      "text": "our economic vitality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 46646.0,
      "end_time": 49445.0,
      "text": "our sense of community and connectedness."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 49974.0,
      "end_time": 53144.0,
      "text": "Fundamentally, the way we shape cities is a manifestation"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53169.0,
      "end_time": 55827.0,
      "text": "of the kind of humanity we bring to bear."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55852.0,
      "end_time": 58961.0,
      "text": "And so getting it right is, I think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 58986.0,
      "end_time": 60632.0,
      "text": "the order of the day."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 60656.0,
      "end_time": 64283.0,
      "text": "And to a certain degree, getting it right can help us solve climate change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 64308.00000000001,
      "end_time": 65460.00000000001,
      "text": "because in the end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 65483.00000000001,
      "end_time": 68911.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s our behavior that seems to be driving the problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 68936.0,
      "end_time": 70814.0,
      "text": "The problem isn&#39;t free-floating,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 70838.0,
      "end_time": 74744.0,
      "text": "and it isn&#39;t just ExxonMobil and oil companies."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74768.0,
      "end_time": 76481.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s us; how we live."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 78161.0,
      "end_time": 79380.0,
      "text": "How we live."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 79864.0,
      "end_time": 81429.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a villain in this story."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 81453.0,
      "end_time": 84966.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s called sprawl, and I&#39;ll be upfront about that."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 84990.0,
      "end_time": 88774.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s not just the kind of sprawl you think of, or many people think of,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 88799.0,
      "end_time": 90429.0,
      "text": "as low-density development"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 90453.0,
      "end_time": 93101.0,
      "text": "out at the periphery of the metropolitan area."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 93952.0,
      "end_time": 98472.0,
      "text": "Actually, I think sprawl can happen anywhere, at any density."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 99160.0,
      "end_time": 102317.0,
      "text": "The key attribute is that it isolates people."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 102874.0,
      "end_time": 106764.0,
      "text": "It segregates people into economic enclaves"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 106788.0,
      "end_time": 108380.0,
      "text": "and land-use enclaves."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 108404.0,
      "end_time": 110500.0,
      "text": "It separates them from nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110524.0,
      "end_time": 113678.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t allow the cross-fertilization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 113702.0,
      "end_time": 114966.0,
      "text": "the interaction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 114990.0,
      "end_time": 117413.0,
      "text": "that make cities great places"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 117437.0,
      "end_time": 119683.0,
      "text": "and that make society thrive."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 120209.0,
      "end_time": 124951.0,
      "text": "So the antidote to sprawl is really what we all need to be thinking about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 124975.0,
      "end_time": 129398.0,
      "text": "especially when we&#39;re taking on this massive construction project."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 129925.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132410.0,
      "text": "So let me take you through one exercise."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 132434.0,
      "end_time": 136200.0,
      "text": "We developed the model for the state of California"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 136224.0,
      "end_time": 139307.0,
      "text": "so they could get on with reducing carbon emissions."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 139866.0,
      "end_time": 145362.0,
      "text": "We did a whole series of scenarios for how the state could grow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 145386.0,
      "end_time": 148509.0,
      "text": "and this is just one overly simplified one."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 148533.0,
      "end_time": 151328.0,
      "text": "We mixed different development prototypes"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 151353.0,
      "end_time": 155164.0,
      "text": "and said they&#39;re going to carry us through the year 2050,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 155188.0,
      "end_time": 159944.0,
      "text": "10 million new crew in our state of California."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 160511.0,
      "end_time": 161763.0,
      "text": "And one was sprawl."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 161787.0,
      "end_time": 165319.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just more of the same: shopping malls, subdivisions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 165343.0,
      "end_time": 166527.0,
      "text": "office parks."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 166551.0,
      "end_time": 170340.0,
      "text": "The other one was dominated by, not everybody moving to the city,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 170365.0,
      "end_time": 172480.0,
      "text": "but just compact development,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 172720.0,
      "end_time": 174630.0,
      "text": "what we used to think of as streetcar suburbs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 174654.0,
      "end_time": 175893.0,
      "text": "walkable neighborhoods,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 175917.0,
      "end_time": 180182.0,
      "text": "low-rise, but integrated, mixed-used environments."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 180789.0,
      "end_time": 183225.0,
      "text": "And the results are astounding."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 183249.0,
      "end_time": 186412.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re astounding not just for the scale of the difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 186436.0,
      "end_time": 190671.0,
      "text": "of this one shift in our city-making habit"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 190695.0,
      "end_time": 195409.0,
      "text": "but also because each one represents a special interest group,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 196530.0,
      "end_time": 200442.0,
      "text": "a special interest group that used to advocate for their concerns"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 200466.0,
      "end_time": 201631.0,
      "text": "one at a time."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 201655.0,
      "end_time": 206754.0,
      "text": "They did not see the, what I call, \"co-benefits\" of urban form"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 206778.0,
      "end_time": 209253.0,
      "text": "that allows them to join with others."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 209277.0,
      "end_time": 210864.0,
      "text": "So, land consumption:"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 210889.0,
      "end_time": 213703.0,
      "text": "environmentalists are really concerned about this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 213727.0,
      "end_time": 214912.0,
      "text": "so are farmers;"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 215516.0,
      "end_time": 217738.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s a whole range of people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 217762.0,
      "end_time": 221149.0,
      "text": "and, of course, neighborhood groups that want open space nearby."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 221681.0,
      "end_time": 223767.0,
      "text": "The sprawl version of California"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 223791.0,
      "end_time": 227417.0,
      "text": "almost doubles the urban physical footprint."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 228249.0,
      "end_time": 230924.0,
      "text": "Greenhouse gas: tremendous savings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 230948.0,
      "end_time": 235763.0,
      "text": "because in California, our biggest carbon emission comes from cars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 235787.0,
      "end_time": 239487.0,
      "text": "and cities that don&#39;t depend on cars as much"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 239511.0,
      "end_time": 242558.0,
      "text": "obviously create huge savings."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 243421.0,
      "end_time": 246497.0,
      "text": "Vehicle miles traveled: that&#39;s what I was just talking about."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 246521.0,
      "end_time": 251506.0,
      "text": "Just reducing the average 10,000 miles per household per year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 251530.0,
      "end_time": 256860.0,
      "text": "from somewhere in the mid-26,000 per household,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 256884.0,
      "end_time": 261764.0,
      "text": "has a huge impact not just on air quality and carbon"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 261788.0,
      "end_time": 264359.0,
      "text": "but also on the household pocketbook."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 264383.0,
      "end_time": 267376.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s very expensive to drive that much,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 267400.0,
      "end_time": 268792.0,
      "text": "and as we&#39;ve seen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 268816.0,
      "end_time": 271330.0,
      "text": "the middle class is struggling to hold on."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 272133.0,
      "end_time": 276118.0,
      "text": "Health care: we were talking about how do you fix it once we broke it --"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 276142.0,
      "end_time": 277301.0,
      "text": "clean the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 277325.0,
      "end_time": 279316.0,
      "text": "Why not just stop polluting?"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 279340.0,
      "end_time": 282768.0,
      "text": "Why not just use our feet and bikes more?"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 282792.0,
      "end_time": 285982.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s a function of the kinds of cities that we shape."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 287134.0,
      "end_time": 288526.0,
      "text": "Household costs:"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 289630.0,
      "end_time": 291361.0,
      "text": "2008 was a mark in time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 291385.0,
      "end_time": 294947.0,
      "text": "not of just the financial industry running amok."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 295463.0,
      "end_time": 300122.0,
      "text": "It was that we were trying to sell too many of the wrong kind of housing:"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 300146.0,
      "end_time": 303970.0,
      "text": "large lot, single family, distant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 303121.0,
      "end_time": 307322.0,
      "text": "too expensive for the average middle-class family to afford"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 307346.0,
      "end_time": 310948.0,
      "text": "and, quite frankly, not a good fit to their lifestyle anymore."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 310972.0,
      "end_time": 312888.0,
      "text": "But in order to move inventory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 313286.0,
      "end_time": 316492.0,
      "text": "you can discount the financing and get it sold."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 316516.0,
      "end_time": 318364.0,
      "text": "I think that&#39;s a lot of what happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 318388.0,
      "end_time": 321540.0,
      "text": "Reducing cost by 10,000 dollars --"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 321780.0,
      "end_time": 323914.0,
      "text": "remember, in California the median is 50,000 --"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 323939.0,
      "end_time": 325820.0,
      "text": "this is a big element."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 325844.0,
      "end_time": 328473.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s just cars and utility costs."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 328497.0,
      "end_time": 332697.0,
      "text": "So the affordable housing advocates, who often sit off in their silos"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 332721.0,
      "end_time": 337185.0,
      "text": "separate from the environmentalists, separate from the politicians,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 337209.0,
      "end_time": 339187.0,
      "text": "everybody fighting with everyone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 339211.0,
      "end_time": 341129.0,
      "text": "now begin to see common cause,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 341153.0,
      "end_time": 344589.0,
      "text": "and I think the common cause is what really brings about the change."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 345657.0,
      "end_time": 348537.0,
      "text": "Los Angeles, as a result of these efforts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 348561.0,
      "end_time": 351585.0,
      "text": "has now decided to transform itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 351609.0,
      "end_time": 354981.0,
      "text": "into a more transit-oriented environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 355500.0,
      "end_time": 356739.0,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, since &#39;08,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 356763.0,
      "end_time": 360712.0,
      "text": "they&#39;ve voted in 400 billion dollars of bonds for transit"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 360736.0,
      "end_time": 363585.0,
      "text": "and zero dollars for new highways."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 363609.0,
      "end_time": 364777.0,
      "text": "What a transformation:"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 364801.0,
      "end_time": 368132.0,
      "text": "LA becomes a city of walkers and transit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 368156.0,
      "end_time": 369335.0,
      "text": "not a city of cars."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 369359.0,
      "end_time": 370366.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 370390.0,
      "end_time": 371590.0,
      "text": "How does it happen?"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 371614.0,
      "end_time": 373751.0,
      "text": "You take the least desirable land, the strip,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 373775.0,
      "end_time": 375822.0,
      "text": "you add where there&#39;s space, transit"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 375846.0,
      "end_time": 380109.0,
      "text": "and then you infill mixed-use development,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 380133.0,
      "end_time": 382316.0,
      "text": "you satisfy new housing demands"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 382340.0,
      "end_time": 384330.0,
      "text": "and you make the existing neighborhoods"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 384355.0,
      "end_time": 385820.0,
      "text": "all around it more complex,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 385844.0,
      "end_time": 387748.0,
      "text": "more interesting, more walkable."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 388660.0,
      "end_time": 390893.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s another kind of sprawl:"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 391607.0,
      "end_time": 395115.0,
      "text": "China, high-density sprawl, what you think of as an oxymoron,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 395139.0,
      "end_time": 398573.0,
      "text": "but the same problems, everything isolated in superblocks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 398597.0,
      "end_time": 402125.0,
      "text": "and of course this amazing smog that was just spoken to."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 402149.0,
      "end_time": 405378.0,
      "text": "Twelve percent of GDP in China now is spent"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 405402.0,
      "end_time": 407599.0,
      "text": "on the health impacts of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 407623.0,
      "end_time": 410888.0,
      "text": "The history, of course, of Chinese cities is robust."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 410912.0,
      "end_time": 412164.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s like any other place."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 412188.0,
      "end_time": 415200.0,
      "text": "Community was all about small, local shops"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 415224.0,
      "end_time": 419366.0,
      "text": "and local services and walking, interacting with your neighbors."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 419391.0,
      "end_time": 421515.0,
      "text": "It may sound utopian, but it&#39;s not."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 421539.0,
      "end_time": 423506.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s actually what people really want."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 423530.0,
      "end_time": 425770.0,
      "text": "The new superblocks --"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 425101.0,
      "end_time": 429210.0,
      "text": "these are blocks that would have 5,000 units in them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 429450.0,
      "end_time": 432857.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re gated as well, because nobody knows anybody else."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 432881.0,
      "end_time": 436381.0,
      "text": "And of course, there isn&#39;t even a sidewalk, no ground floor shops --"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 436405.0,
      "end_time": 438268.0,
      "text": "a very sterile environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 438838.0,
      "end_time": 443454.0,
      "text": "I found this one case here in one of the superblocks"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 443478.0,
      "end_time": 446704.0,
      "text": "where people had illicitly set up shops in their garages"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 446728.0,
      "end_time": 450426.0,
      "text": "so that they could have that kind of local service economy."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 450450.0,
      "end_time": 455207.0,
      "text": "The desire of people to get it right is there."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 455231.0,
      "end_time": 458519.0,
      "text": "We just have to get the planners on board and the politicians."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 458982.0,
      "end_time": 462789.0,
      "text": "All right. Some technical planning stuff."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 462813.0,
      "end_time": 465986.0,
      "text": "Chongqing is a city of 30 million people."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 466100.0,
      "end_time": 468373.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s almost as big as California."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 468397.0,
      "end_time": 470870.0,
      "text": "This is a small growth area."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 470111.0,
      "end_time": 473723.0,
      "text": "They wanted us to test the alternative to sprawl"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 473747.0,
      "end_time": 476521.0,
      "text": "in several cities across China."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 476892.0,
      "end_time": 480174.0,
      "text": "This is for four-and-a-half million people."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 480198.0,
      "end_time": 482128.0,
      "text": "What the takeaway from this image is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 482153.0,
      "end_time": 484802.0,
      "text": "every one of those circles is a walking radius"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 484826.0,
      "end_time": 486442.0,
      "text": "around a transit station --"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 487100.0,
      "end_time": 490550.0,
      "text": "massive investment in metro and BRT,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 490764.0,
      "end_time": 493960.0,
      "text": "and a distribution that allows everybody"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 493120.0,
      "end_time": 495731.0,
      "text": "to work within walking distance of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 495755.0,
      "end_time": 498520.0,
      "text": "The red area, this is a blow-up."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 498760.0,
      "end_time": 501233.0,
      "text": "All of a sudden, our principles called for green space"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 501257.0,
      "end_time": 504947.0,
      "text": "preserving the important ecological features."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 504971.0,
      "end_time": 509298.0,
      "text": "And then those other streets in there are auto-free streets."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 509322.0,
      "end_time": 512945.0,
      "text": "So instead of bulldozing, leveling the site"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 512969.00000000006,
      "end_time": 515320.00000000006,
      "text": "and building right up to the river,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 515559.99999999994,
      "end_time": 519279.99999999994,
      "text": "this green edge was something that really wasn&#39;t normative in China"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 519304.0,
      "end_time": 521875.0,
      "text": "until these set of practices"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 521899.0,
      "end_time": 524453.0,
      "text": "began experimentation there."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 524883.0,
      "end_time": 526838.0,
      "text": "The urban fabric, small blocks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 526862.0,
      "end_time": 529478.0,
      "text": "maybe 500 families per block."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 529502.0,
      "end_time": 530771.0,
      "text": "They know each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 530795.0,
      "end_time": 533158.0,
      "text": "The street perimeter has shops"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 533182.0,
      "end_time": 535104.0,
      "text": "so there&#39;s local destinations."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 535128.0,
      "end_time": 537483.0,
      "text": "And the streets themselves become smaller,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 537507.0,
      "end_time": 539360.0,
      "text": "because there are more of them."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 539610.0,
      "end_time": 540612.0,
      "text": "Very simple,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 540636.0,
      "end_time": 543190.0,
      "text": "straightforward urban design."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 543215.0,
      "end_time": 546425.0,
      "text": "Now, here you have something I dearly love."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 546449.0,
      "end_time": 547723.0,
      "text": "Think of the logic."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 548172.0,
      "end_time": 550319.0,
      "text": "If only a third of the people have cars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 550343.0,
      "end_time": 554107.0,
      "text": "why do we give 100 percent of our streets to cars?"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 554748.0,
      "end_time": 557927.0,
      "text": "What if we gave 70 percent of the streets"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 557951.0,
      "end_time": 560126.0,
      "text": "to car-free, to everybody else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 560150.0,
      "end_time": 562395.0,
      "text": "so that the transit could move well for them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 562419.0,
      "end_time": 564744.0,
      "text": "so that they could walk, so they could bike?"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 564768.0,
      "end_time": 566166.0,
      "text": "Why not have --"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 566190.0,
      "end_time": 567643.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 567667.0,
      "end_time": 569820.0,
      "text": "geographic equity"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 569844.0,
      "end_time": 572215.0,
      "text": "in our circulation system?"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 572518.0,
      "end_time": 575911.0,
      "text": "And quite frankly, cities would function better."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 576300.0,
      "end_time": 577589.0,
      "text": "No matter what they do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 577614.0,
      "end_time": 580440.0,
      "text": "no matter how many ring roads they build in Beijing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 580680.0,
      "end_time": 582996.0,
      "text": "they just can&#39;t overcome complete gridlock."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 583200.0,
      "end_time": 586708.0,
      "text": "So this is an auto-free street, mixed use along the edge."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 587486.0,
      "end_time": 589345.0,
      "text": "It has transit running down the middle."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 589369.0,
      "end_time": 592473.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m happy to make that transit autonomous vehicles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 592497.0,
      "end_time": 595406.0,
      "text": "but maybe I&#39;ll have a chance to talk about that later."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 595431.0,
      "end_time": 599154.0,
      "text": "So there are seven principles that have now been adopted"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 599178.0,
      "end_time": 601878.0,
      "text": "by the highest levels in the Chinese government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 601902.0,
      "end_time": 603697.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re moving to implement them."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 603721.0,
      "end_time": 604883.0,
      "text": "And they&#39;re simple,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 604907.0,
      "end_time": 607520.0,
      "text": "and they are globally, I think, universal principles."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 607544.0,
      "end_time": 611197.0,
      "text": "One is to preserve the natural environment, the history"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 611221.0,
      "end_time": 613188.0,
      "text": "and the critical agriculture."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 614126.0,
      "end_time": 615449.0,
      "text": "Second is mix."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 615473.0,
      "end_time": 617990.0,
      "text": "Mixed use is popular, but when I say mixed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 618140.0,
      "end_time": 620453.0,
      "text": "I mean mixed incomes, mixed age groups"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 620477.0,
      "end_time": 622968.0,
      "text": "as well as mixed-land use."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 624100.0,
      "end_time": 625164.0,
      "text": "Walk."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 625188.0,
      "end_time": 628208.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s no great city that you don&#39;t enjoy walking in."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 628232.0,
      "end_time": 629550.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t go there."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 629574.0,
      "end_time": 632126.0,
      "text": "The places you go on vacation are places you can walk."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 632150.0,
      "end_time": 633911.0,
      "text": "Why not make it everywhere?"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 634381.0,
      "end_time": 637953.0,
      "text": "Bike is the most efficient means of transportation we know."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 638326.0,
      "end_time": 642740.0,
      "text": "China has now adopted policies that put six meters of bike lane"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 642980.0,
      "end_time": 643426.0,
      "text": "on every street."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 643451.0,
      "end_time": 647393.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re serious about getting back to their biking history."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 647417.0,
      "end_time": 648873.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 648897.0,
      "end_time": 651200.0,
      "text": "Complicated planner-ese here:"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 651224.0,
      "end_time": 652553.0,
      "text": "connect."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 652577.0,
      "end_time": 656890.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a street network that allows many routes"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 656113.0,
      "end_time": 657924.0,
      "text": "instead of singular routes"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 657948.0,
      "end_time": 661495.0,
      "text": "and provides many kinds of streets instead of just one."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 662572.0,
      "end_time": 663916.0,
      "text": "Ride."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 663940.0,
      "end_time": 666250.0,
      "text": "We have to invest more in transit."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 666274.0,
      "end_time": 668490.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s no silver bullet."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 668730.0,
      "end_time": 671137.0,
      "text": "Autonomous vehicles are not going to solve this for us."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 671161.0,
      "end_time": 676327.0,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, they&#39;re going to generate more traffic, more VMT,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 676351.0,
      "end_time": 677713.0,
      "text": "than the alternative."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 677737.0,
      "end_time": 678951.0,
      "text": "And focus."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 678975.0,
      "end_time": 683131.0,
      "text": "We have a hierarchy of the city based on transit"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 683155.0,
      "end_time": 686318.0,
      "text": "rather than the old armature of freeways."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 686342.0,
      "end_time": 688492.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a big paradigm shift,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 689650.0,
      "end_time": 691732.0,
      "text": "but those two things have to get reconnected"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 691756.0,
      "end_time": 696276.0,
      "text": "in ways that really shape the structure of the city."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 697263.0,
      "end_time": 699496.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;m very hopeful."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 699520.0,
      "end_time": 704293.0,
      "text": "In California, the United States, China -- these changes are well accepted."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 704317.0,
      "end_time": 706952.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m hopeful for two reasons."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 706976.0,
      "end_time": 709550.0,
      "text": "One is, most people get it."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 709790.0,
      "end_time": 710960.0,
      "text": "They understand intrinsically"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 710985.0,
      "end_time": 713627.0,
      "text": "what a great city can and should be."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 713651.0,
      "end_time": 718492.0,
      "text": "The second is that the kind of analysis we can bring to bear now"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 718516.0,
      "end_time": 721243.0,
      "text": "allows people to connect the dots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 721756.0,
      "end_time": 724725.0,
      "text": "allows people to shape political coalitions"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 724749.0,
      "end_time": 726178.0,
      "text": "that didn&#39;t exist in the past."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 726539.0,
      "end_time": 730279.0,
      "text": "That allows them to bring into being the kinds of communities we all need."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 730303.0,
      "end_time": 731492.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 731516.0,
      "end_time": 738930.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 739838.0,
      "end_time": 743275.0,
      "text": "Chris Anderson: So, OK: autonomous driving, self-driving cars."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 743299.0,
      "end_time": 746644.0,
      "text": "A lot of people here are very excited about them."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 747263.0,
      "end_time": 750222.0,
      "text": "What are your concerns or issues about them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 750246.0,
      "end_time": 753388.0,
      "text": "Peter Calthorpe: Well, I think there&#39;s almost too much hype here."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 753412.0,
      "end_time": 756986.0,
      "text": "First is, everybody says we&#39;re going to get rid of a lot of cars."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 757100.0,
      "end_time": 760304.0,
      "text": "What they don&#39;t say is you&#39;re going to get a lot more vehicle miles."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 760328.0,
      "end_time": 762875.0,
      "text": "You&#39;re going to get a lot more cars moving on streets."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 762899.0,
      "end_time": 764768.0,
      "text": "There will be more congestion."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 764792.0,
      "end_time": 767100.0,
      "text": "CA: Because they&#39;re so appealing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 767124.0,
      "end_time": 769178.0,
      "text": "you can drive while reading or sleeping."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 769202.0,
      "end_time": 770699.0,
      "text": "PC: Well, a couple of reasons."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 770723.0,
      "end_time": 774694.0,
      "text": "One is, if they&#39;re privately owned, people will travel greater distances."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 774718.0,
      "end_time": 776659.0,
      "text": "It&#39;ll be a new lease on life to sprawl."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 776683.0,
      "end_time": 778698.0,
      "text": "If you can work on your way to work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 778722.0,
      "end_time": 780789.0,
      "text": "you can live in more remote locations."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 780813.0,
      "end_time": 783355.0,
      "text": "It&#39;ll revitalize sprawl"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 783379.0,
      "end_time": 785712.0,
      "text": "in a way that I&#39;m deeply frightened."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 785736.0,
      "end_time": 787590.0,
      "text": "Taxis:"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 787614.0,
      "end_time": 791362.0,
      "text": "about 50 percent of the surveys say that people won&#39;t share them."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 791386.0,
      "end_time": 792760.0,
      "text": "If they don&#39;t share them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 792784.0,
      "end_time": 797981.0,
      "text": "you can end up with a 90 percent increase in vehicle miles traveled."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 798417.0,
      "end_time": 799738.0,
      "text": "If you share them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 799762.0,
      "end_time": 803291.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re still at around a 30 percent increase in VMT."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 803316.0,
      "end_time": 806354.0,
      "text": "CA: Sharing them, meaning having multiple people riding at once"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 806378.0,
      "end_time": 808354.0,
      "text": "in some sort of intelligent ride-sharing?"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 808378.0,
      "end_time": 810909.0,
      "text": "PC: Yeah, so the Uber share without a steering wheel."
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 810933.0,
      "end_time": 814782.0,
      "text": "The reality is, the efficiency of vehicles -- you can do it"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 814806.0,
      "end_time": 817297.0,
      "text": "with or without a steering wheel, it doesn&#39;t matter."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 817321.0,
      "end_time": 820814.0,
      "text": "They claim they&#39;re the only ones that are going to be efficient electric,"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 820838.0,
      "end_time": 821992.0,
      "text": "but that&#39;s not true."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 822160.0,
      "end_time": 825586.0,
      "text": "But the real bottom line is that walking, biking and transit"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 825610.0,
      "end_time": 828774.0,
      "text": "are the way cities and communities thrive."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 828798.0,
      "end_time": 831605.0,
      "text": "And putting people in their private bubbles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 831629.0,
      "end_time": 833926.0,
      "text": "whether they have a steering wheel or not,"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 833950.0,
      "end_time": 835521.0,
      "text": "is the wrong direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 835545.0,
      "end_time": 836695.0,
      "text": "And quite frankly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 836720.0,
      "end_time": 842399.0,
      "text": "the image of an AV on its way to McDonald&#39;s to pick up a pack"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 842423.0,
      "end_time": 844107.0,
      "text": "without its owner,"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 844131.0,
      "end_time": 847841.0,
      "text": "just being sent off on these kind of random errands"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 847865.0,
      "end_time": 849262.0,
      "text": "is really frightening to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 849286.0,
      "end_time": 852643.0,
      "text": "CA: Well, thank you for that, and I have to say, the images you showed"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 852668.0,
      "end_time": 855844.0,
      "text": "of those mixed-use streets were really inspiring, really beautiful."
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 855868.0,
      "end_time": 858270.0,
      "text": "PC: Thank you. CA: Thank you for your work."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 858510.0,
      "end_time": 859510.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}